<p>I want to write a rule in htaccess that always redirects <code>http://example.com/index.aspx</code> or <code>http://www.example.com/index.aspx</code> to <code>http://example.com</code>.</p>  <p>This is what I have tried so far: </p>  <pre><code>RewriteCond %{REQUEST_URI} ^/index.aspx [NC] RewriteRule ^(.*)$ http://%1 [R=301,L] </code></pre>  <p>but it's not working properly.</p>  <p>Thanks</p>